column2: Most common values:    Chronometric Age Protocol (1x)
Most common values:    A description of or reference to the methods used to determine the chronometric age. (1x)
Notes or comments about the ChronometricAge. (1x)
The temporal uncertainty of the earliestChronometricAge and latestChronometicAge in years. (1x)
The maximum/earliest/oldest possible age of a specimen as determined by a dating method. (1x)
The reference system associated with the earliestChronometricAge. (1x)
Contains null values:  True (excluded from calculations)
The minimum/latest/youngest possible age of an object in the collection as determined by a dating method. (1x)
The verbatim age for the objects in the collection, whether reported by a dating assay, associated references, or legacy information. (1x)
Contains null values:  True (excluded from calculations)

The expected unit for this field is years. The value in this field is number of years before and after the values given in the earliest and latest chronometric age fields within which the actual values are estimated to be. (1x)
The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated earliestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem. (1x)
The expected unit for this field is years. This field, if populated, must have an associated latestChronometricAgeReferenceSystem. (1x)
Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. (1x)
